      "content": "It's possible that the remaining symptoms, despite rehydrating, could be related to electrolyte imbalances. Electrolytes, such as sodium and potassium, play a crucial role in proper brain function. Taking an electrolyte supplement could help alleviate the foggy feeling, but consider visiting a local pharmacy or a clinic to get advice from a medical professional before taking any supplements. In the meantime, try to rest and monitor your condition closely.",
