      "content": "While electrolyte supplements can help alleviate hydration-related issues, double-upping on them might not be enough to address the brain fog. Electrolytes can't directly affect cognitive function, and excessive consumption may lead to gastrointestinal issues or interact with other medications. Instead, consider taking a moderate dose of electrolyte powder and staying hydrated, and see if your symptoms improve. If the brain fog persists, it's still worth consulting a medical professional to rule out other potential causes.",
